text:
Trying out this new brunch western stall that was the talkabout in FB posting. Verdict :-
chicken chop sandwich ⭐️⭐️⭐️$6.90
Waffle chicken ⭐️⭐️⭐️$8.90
Hungry Breakfast ⭐️⭐️$9.90

Was there around 2pm & still many customers. So Be patient to wait coz not enough ppl in the kitchen.
Friendly staffs! Their yuan yang is great! Try their iced lime tea too! Also can try their watermelon juice! Their breakfast sets is great! Especially their toasted bread!
Went for Nasi Lemak again after 3 years. Taste okay but price very high now. No parking space.

Went there to eat Punggol Nasi Lemak.

Coconut rice, he bi hiam, archar, and the chicken wings and drumsticks are must buys.
Drink is extremely expensive and dilute. All Milo/teh/lemon tea are all very dilute and watery taste.
